   <mods:abstract>Writes Wadsworth (at Hartford) asking him to send to Mrs. Jay "a pattern
            of a gown and petticoat, of some grave quaker color" of the excellent silks they have
            heard are available in Wallingford. "Cloths" have arrived. Jay will see them next day
            and take a suit. "If it should become fashionable to prefer our own manufactures, their
            Progress will be greatly advanced by it; especially if we come to consider whatever is
            American as our own..."</mods:abstract>
